// Epilogue

COPY ~%MOD_FOLDER%/Epilogue/C0AuEpzz.2da~ ~override/C0AuEp01.2da~
REPLACE ~99999~ ~After the end of Aura's journey with <CHARNAME> came a difficult parting. Though the first to shed tears upon bidding her friends farewell, Aura's departure was memorated with a smile and a promise to always remain in touch and be there to help once again, should the need ever come. The epic journey had sparked newfound courage within Aura, and so she travelled to lands alone in search of new knowledge and treasured memories, meeting many famed heroes and villains alike on the way, though none would ever match those she encountered alongside her greatest friend and leader. Eventually, when wanderlust made way for a lasting homesickness, Aura returned to Lantan, and was greeted with a tremendous audience in her hometown of Anchoril composed to admirers, old classmates, and her beloved family at the head who welcomed her home with a firm embrace. In the months following, scholars and artificers from all across the nation sought Aura for her knowledge, and she was more than happy to fulfill her duty in advancing Lantan to a whole new age.

Countless inventions and curiosities that were beyond imagination soon spread throughout the land, but no decision made more impact than Aura's sudden and unexpected proposal to the council for building Lantan's first magical academy, a place where those with a belief in the harmony of invention and magic could make even greater discoveries. With little hesistation, she was answered with an unanimous agreement by the Ayrorch, and two years later Aurelia Glimmershine was officially recognized as Decanus Primus of the First College of Thaumaturgy, promoting the study of magical artifice to future generations of aspiring arcanists from both Lantan and abroad—a few even coming as far as from the eastern lands, brought back to the college by the Decanus during her occasional 'field studies'. A grandiose painting was displayed in the academy's main hall, though students spoke less of the Decanus's portrayal and more of the image of the <PRO_MANWOMAN> at her side, an addition purportedly requested by Aura herself. When asked about her relation to the legendary figure, she would simply smile brightly and point at the inscription under their name: "The original teacher, and the greatest".~

COPY ~%MOD_FOLDER%/Epilogue/C0AuEpzz.2da~ ~override/C0AuEp02.2da~
REPLACE ~99999~ ~After the end of Aura's journey with <CHARNAME> came a difficult parting, though she would not walk her future path entirely alone, as she would be inevitably be cajoled by her close companion Imoen into many new adventures. After a brief sojourn to the citadel of Candlekeep, the two would later be known for having been in the midst of several realm-shaking events—some, of course, being a direct result of Imoen's penchant for mischief and excessive curiosity, with a beleaguered Aura always at her side. One such tall tale spoke of the two in the middle of a tremendous crater of unknown cause where a fortress of the Cult of the Dragon once stood, sitting by a picnic basket and sharing biscuits without a care in the world before happily setting off to their next venture. Wherever Imoen went, Aura followed, and the two became famed not only for their knowledge and power, but also their bond as the ideal partners in crime—of the justified sort, Imoen would frequently emphasize, to which Aura would always respond with an exasperated sigh.

Though their shared adventures were both thrilling and purposeful, however, Aura's thoughts eventually strayed back to Lantan only her longing for it, but also her desire to use her skills to change her home for the better. Imoen, who valued her partner's happiness more than the excitement of the road, followed her back to the land of invention, where she was introduced to the Glimmershines, with her optimistic charm and quick mind quickly endearing herself to all of Aura's family. Their presence in Lantan quickly became the talk of the entire nation, with countless scholars and artificers seeking them for an exchange of knowledge. Imoen would even briefly study within the Sambaran academy, becoming a favorite pupil of several professors even despite her countless pranks.

When Imoen eventually felt the call of the road once more, Aura became torn between her responsibility to stay and help Lantan and her desire to follow her partner. Imoen, knowing her conflicting wishes, encouraged her to stay while sharing a promise to always remain in touch, and their farewell—embellished with an embrace and a surprise kiss from Imoen—left Aura memorably flustered in front of her siblings and parents. She would also take Aura's brother, Eridanus, along with her as an apprentice on their journey. Coming to greatly miss Imoen over time and inspired by her dedication to the Art, Aura decided to make a proposal to the council for building Lantan's first magical academy, a place where those with a belief in the harmony of invention and magic could make even greater discoveries. With little hesistation, she was answered with an unanimous agreement by the Ayrorch, and two years later Aurelia Glimmershine was officially recognized as Decanus Primus of the First College of Thaumaturgy, promoting the study of magical artifice to future generations of aspiring arcanists from both Lantan and abroad. Imoen would later visit the college herself, occasionally serving as a professor who as respected and adored by her students, eagerly recounting many questions on her adventures, her acquaintance with figures such as Elminster and Khelben Arunsun, though she would be more reserved as to her personal relationship with the Decanus. Though their respective professions meant the two spent more time apart than together, none could argue that their bond was any less meaningful for it.~

COPY ~%MOD_FOLDER%/Epilogue/C0AuEpzz.2da~ ~override/C0AuEp03.2da~
REPLACE ~99999~ ~With <CHARNAME>'s destiny fulfilled and the Bhaalspawn crisis at its end, it was time for the next chapter of her story to begin, and there was no doubt that Aura would be at her side, delighted by her partner's decision to remain mortal and share in their joy in their remaining lives. With her newfound determination from having put the last of her doubts and fears to rest, Aura fearlessly and determinedly followed <CHARNAME> throughout countless adventures, and the inspiration nurtured from the journey led her to achieve even greater heights in her practice of magical artifice. New inventions and theorems spread throughout the scholarly circles of the realms and planted the seeds that would guide Faerûn into a new and brighter age. <CHARNAME>'s unerring support and guidance bolstered Aura's determination to ensure that knowledge would be used righteously and for the better of all mortals, and the duo would journey throughout the Realms to combat the rise of those who sought knowledge for evil intent, earning the alliance of benevolent forces such as the Harpers and the dread of nefarious organizations both. Though Aura longed to live in a world of harmony and understanding, she knew the path to it would be long, if not beyond her lifetime, yet her conviction never failed—nor would it ever be so long as her beloved <CHARNAME> was with her.

In time, <CHARNAME> and Aura would find an occasional chance for peace as they saw the seeds of their labors bear fruit, and they would make the journey to their respective homes together for a respite, beginning with the great citadel of Candlekeep—where the now-famous Aura was nearly smothered by the masses of monks seeking an audience in what would perhaps be the most raucous day the library has seen in generations—and then the nation of Lantan, where <CHARNAME> was embraced by Aura's loving family as though one of their own. Within the first month of their time in Aura's homeland, she and <CHARNAME> wed in a small but energetic ceremony officiated by her sister Luna, and as per Lantanese tradition, the feast was embellished by the exchange of countless new and ongoing projects shared by the excited scholars and inventors in attendance. The next week, the Lantanese council approved of Aura and <CHARNAME>'s proposal to start the first college of magic within Lantan, and the nation would soon be forever changed by the upsurge in study of magical artifice over the following generations.

Having set the foundations for a greater future for both her home and the realms, Aura finally felt a sense of satisfaction, and the proper courage to take one more long-awaited journey, with <CHARNAME> naturally at her side, towards Kozakura in the far east. In the peaceful island in Mikedono, seemingly unchanged in all the years spent away, Aura brought <CHARNAME> to her brief home at the shrine of Amatsugami, where the two paid their respects to her late mentor and guardian's grave, a visit which would soon become a tradition they underwent once each year. As Aura bowed before the white headstone and looked towards the cherry trees in the garden, she would reminisce with <CHARNAME> over the long and troubled, yet ultimately blessed, road that led her this far... and with a smile as she took <CHARNAME>'s hand and turned away, earnestly agreed that no matter what, she would not have exchanged it for any other.~

COPY ~%MOD_FOLDER%/Epilogue/C0AuEpzz.2da~ ~override/C0AuEp04.2da~
REPLACE ~99999~ ~With <CHARNAME>'s ascension upon the Throne of Bhaal, Aura felt a lasting sense of melancholy, yet she knew that, in a way, the woman she fell in love with would always be with her still, and so she set forth on her next journey with the courage that comes from knowing that her beloved would be watching over her. Determined to make her own lasting mark upon the realms as a force for good, she travelled to lands alone in search of new knowledge and treasured memories, meeting many famed heroes and villains alike on the way, encountering many dangers but escaping the clutches of death every time—with many attributing her unnatural fortune to the watchful eye of a deity that favored her. Eventually, when wanderlust made way for a lasting homesickness, Aura returned to Lantan, and was greeted with a tremendous audience in her hometown of Anchoril composed to admirers, old classmates, and her beloved family at the head who welcomed her home with a firm embrace. In the months following, scholars and artificers from all across the nation sought Aura for her knowledge, and she was more than happy to fulfill her duty in advancing Lantan to a whole new age.

Countless inventions and curiosities that were beyond imagination soon spread throughout the land, but no decision made more impact than Aura's sudden and unexpected proposal to the council for building Lantan's first magical academy, a place where those with a belief in the harmony of invention and magic could make even greater discoveries. With little hesistation, she was answered with an unanimous agreement by the Ayrorch, and two years later Aurelia Glimmershine was officially recognized as Decanus Primus of the First College of Thaumaturgy, promoting the study of magical artifice to future generations of aspiring arcanists from both Lantan and abroad—a few even coming as far as from the eastern lands, brought back to the college by the Decanus during her occasional 'field studies'. A grandiose painting was displayed in the academy's main hall, though students spoke less of the Decanus's portrayal and more of the image of the woman at her side, which Aura herself would unfailingly contemplate with a wistful gaze on each day. When asked by inquisitive students as to the figure's resemblance to depictions of a young goddess, and her relation with said entity, she would merely respond with a sad smile, responding as thus: "Many look towards her light, but she has never shone more brightly than as I remembered her, and one day... I know I'll see it again."~

