With this ability, an artificer may attempt to create a Lantanese Autocannon in the targeted location. The success of the ability is dependent on the artificer's Set Traps skill. This autocannon will become active upon an enemy creature entering its range. The autocannon is immobile and launches fiery missiles dealing 1d2 fire damage.

Automatons have a 5% chance per round to become Overcharged, becoming Hasted and launching missiles at twice their normal rate.

For each 15 points of Set Traps above 100 from the artificer, autocannons gain a +1 bonus to Armor Class and +5 bonus hit points.
For each 50 points of Set Traps above 100 from the artificer, autocannons deal 1 additional point of fire damage.

Once activated, autocannons last for two turns.~
